<p><b>What level of math is linear algebra?</b> Linear algebra comes way after intermediate algebra. In most cases, although not necessarily all cases, linear algebra also involves calculus. The typical progression (not sure where you are exactly) would be High School algebra (completed), Calculus (differentiation and integration) then Linear Algebra.</p>
<p><b>What is the hardest math class?</b> What is the Hardest Math Class in High School? In most cases, you'll find that AP Calculus BC or IB Math HL is the most difficult math course your school offers. Note that AP Calculus BC covers the material in AP Calculus AB but also continues the curriculum, addressing more challenging and advanced concepts.</p>
<p><b>Is linear algebra the most useful math?</b> Linear algebra is central to almost all areas of mathematics. For instance, linear algebra is fundamental in modern presentations of geometry, including for defining basic objects such as lines, planes and rotations.</p>
